      <hedline>
        <hl1>Subtract the Ads</hl1>
      </hedline>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Sports Editor:</p>
        <p>First, they took down the facade at Yankee Stadium. Then, they disturbed the outfield dimensions. Next, they made nearly all field-level seats the exclusive property of the landed gentry. For good measure, nearly all games are unavailable on Channel 11.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Sports Editor:</p>
        <p>First, they took down the facade at Yankee Stadium. Then, they disturbed the outfield dimensions. Next, they made nearly all field-level seats the exclusive property of the landed gentry. For good measure, nearly all games are unavailable on Channel 11.</p>
        <p>Now, the center-field camera on opening day showed we are to be subjected to advertising, behind home plate, with every pitch.</p>
        <p>Is this the final insult? Probably not. BEN CALDERONE  Levittown, L.I.</p>
      </block>
